Understand about sort and compare an array.
---->
 
 Sorting an Array: The sort method sorts the elements of an array in place and returns the sorted array. By default, it sorts elements as strings.

  campare callback function...
 // syntax:
  const sortedNumber = number.sort((a,b) => a-b);
  if(a>b) return 1 => switch the order.
  if(b>a) return -1 => keep the order.

 callback: A function that is called once for each element in the array.
 accumulator: The accumulated result of the previous iterations.
 currentValue: The current element being processed in the array.
 index (optional): The index of the current element being processed.
 array (optional): The array reduce was called upon.
 initialValue (optional): An initial value for the accumulator. If not provided, the first element of the array is used as the initial accumulator value.

 code--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
 // sorting of array.......
const fruits = ["Banana", "Apple", "Orange", "Mango"];
fruits.sort();
console.log(fruits);  // output [ 'Apple', 'Banana', 'Mango', 'Orange' ]
// remember most of the time with numbers we cannot do for large data (numbers) it will wrong.

// compare callback function.....
  const number = [1,2,3,5,4,7,6,8,9];
  number.sort((a,b) => {   // for ascending order
    if(a>b) return 1;
    if (b>a) return -1;
  })
  console.log(number);

// output  1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9  // sorted

// if want in dereasing order.then change the order.
number.sort((a,b) => {    // for desending order.
    if(a>b) return -1;
    if (b>a) return 1;
  })
  console.log(number);

  //output  9, 8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1
